The enhancement in the generation rate of photoinduced charge carriers is strongly related to the reduction of optical bandgap of CoFe2O4. Optical bandgap of CoFe2O4 nanostructure film has been determined using CoFe2O4 nanostructure film coated onto a quartz substrate. Figure 3a show the optical bandgap of CoFe2O4 nanostructure film under different magnetic field strengths determined by using the Tauc relation31–33;2(αhv)2=A(hv−Eg)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
