				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${(\alpha hv)}^{2}={\rm{A}}(hv-{E}_{g})$$\end{document}where, A is a constant, α is the absorption coefficient, hv is the absorbed photon energy and Eg is the optical bandgap.Figure 3
(a) Optical bandgap results of CoFe2O4 nanostructure film under different magnetic field strengths, (b) variation of bandgap with magnetic field, (c) Raman spectroscopy results of CoFe2O4 film under different magnetic field strengths, (d) variation of intensity ratio (Iv) with magnetic field.

